@Solve Everything There is no need to be so abrasive. It's true that western society seems to almost have a fetish for higher education when in reality you'll spend a lot of time being bombarded with concepts and ideas that are high level abstractions which difficult to apply to anything but a very narrow field of work.

Whether or not you think higher education has any worth is totally based on goals and values. You need college to become a lawyer or doctor. You really don't if you want to start a business or to program apps.

It's a value judgment based on a wide variety of variables. It depends on what college means to you. Who you're trying to impress and what you want out of life.
